---
import Legal from '../../components/Legal.astro'
import { SITE, MAILTO } from '../../consts'
---

<Legal
  lang="en"
  kind="privacy"
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How your data is handled on anthonyeca.dev: no cookies, no analytics, full transparency."
  updated="June 24, 2026"
>
  <h2>1. Data controller</h2>
  <p>
    The controller responsible for the data collected through this website is
    <strong>Anthony Challout</strong> (the “Controller”), owner of
    <a href="https://anthonyeca.dev">anthonyeca.dev</a>.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Contact: <a href={MAILTO}>{SITE.email}</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. What data we process</h2>
  <p>
    This is an informational website that <strong>uses no cookies, no analytics tools and no
    forms</strong>. We do not build profiles or track your browsing. In practice, personal data is
    only processed in two situations:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Technical connection data.</strong> To serve the site and protect it against attacks,
      our hosting provider automatically logs technical data such as your IP address, browser type and
      the date and time of access, for security and operational purposes.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Contact data.</strong> If you email us, we process the data you provide (name, email
      address and the content of your message) in order to handle your request.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Purpose and legal basis</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Security and service delivery</strong> (technical data): the Controller's legitimate
      interest (Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR) in keeping the site secure and operational.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Handling enquiries</strong> (contact data): your consent when you contact us and, where
      applicable, pre-contractual measures taken at your request (Art. 6(1)(a) and 6(1)(b) GDPR).
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Retention</h2>
  <p>
    Contact data is kept for as long as necessary to handle your request and thereafter for any legally
    required periods. The hosting provider's technical logs are kept for short periods in line with its
    security policies.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Recipients</h2>
  <p>
    We do not sell or share your data with third parties. To operate, the site relies on the following
    providers acting as processors:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cloudflare, Inc.</strong> — hosting and content delivery network (CDN).</li>
    <li><strong>Google LLC</strong> — the contact mailbox is handled through Gmail.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    These providers may process data on servers located outside the European Economic Area. In such
    cases, international transfers are covered by the appropriate safeguards provided for under the GDPR
    (such as the EU-US Data Privacy Framework or the European Commission's standard contractual clauses).
  </p>

  <h2>6. Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    You may exercise your rights of access, rectification, erasure, objection, restriction of
    processing and data portability at any time by writing to <a href={MAILTO}>{SITE.email}</a>. If you
    believe the processing does not comply with the applicable rules, you have the right to lodge a
    complaint with the Spanish Data Protection Agency
    (<a href="https://www.aepd.es" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.aepd.es</a>).
  </p>

  <h2>7. Cookies</h2>
  <p>
    This site <strong>does not install cookies</strong> or similar tracking technologies on your
    device. For this reason, no cookie banner is shown.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Automated decisions</h2>
  <p>No automated decision-making or profiling is carried out with your data.</p>

  <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    This policy may be updated to reflect legal or operational changes to the site. The date of the
    last update is shown at the top of this page.
  </p>
</Legal>
